What does a segue do? How do you use it and where?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qr\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 >> A segue allows for a transition between two view controllers in your storyboard. The segue begins at the view that has an action done to it, like a button or tapping on a table row. The end point of the segue is which view controller you want to display. You use it by control-clicking on the starting point and dragging it to the target view controller. When you release the click, select the transition you want (we have been using \'93Show\'94). 
\b \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
